cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS 

This paper deals with optimizing the Radio Access Network (RAN) of cellular networks, which falls under the category of Networked and Internet Systems (cs.NI). The paper proposes algorithms for clustering users based on Device-to-Device (D2D) communications, which involves optimizing the use of network resources, and hence falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with load balancing and energy efficiency, which are aspects of System and Control (cs.SY). The paper uses simulations to evaluate the proposed algorithms, which involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data, and hence falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms that involve optimization and trade-offs, which are aspects of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
